.TH "getLastOut" "1" "" "SequoiaDB User Manuals" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
getLastOut \- Get the result of the last command execution.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]\f[I]getLastOut()\f[]\f[]
.SH CATEGORY
.PP
Cmd
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Get the result of the last command execution.
.SH PARAMETERS
.PP
NULL
.SH RETURN VALUE
.PP
On success, return the object information of the Command object.
.PP
On error, exception will be thrown.
.SH ERRORS
.PP
when exception happen, use getLastError() to get the error code and use
getLastErrMsg() to get error message.
For more detial, please reference to Troubleshooting.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP \[bu] 2
Create a Command object.
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
>\ var\ cmd\ =\ new\ Cmd()
\f[]
.fi
.IP \[bu] 2
Executed command(For more detial on Command Object executed command, please
reference to Cmd::run)
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
>\ cmd.run(\ "ls",\ "/opt/trunk/test"\ )
test1
test2
test3
\f[]
.fi
.IP \[bu] 2
Get the result of the last command execution.
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
>\ cmd.getLastOut()
test1
test2
test3
\f[]
.fi
